The Customs Bureau has begun to levyon bond on certain Japanese goods pending a final decision byPresident Reagan on April 17 on imposing the planned 100 pcttariff on the shipments, the bureau said.    A bureau official said bonding began on March 31 and if thepenalties are imposed as expected after a period of comment,they will retroactive to that date.    The penalties are to be levied on variety of electronicitems in retaliation for Japan's failure to comply with a July1986 agreement to end dumping semiconductors in third nationsand to open its home market to U.S. goods. reuter&#3;